<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-12-16T18:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-12-16T18:36:00-05:00" n="180" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d180">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/588: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-16T17:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">December 16,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 11:30
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>54. Minister of Foreign Affairs and First and Second Designados and
                            certain other prisoners released. Escamilla only member of Cabinet held
                            in prison. Situation improving.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>